title: For Sale/Trade:  non running 1977 BMW R100/7
postcontent: For sale is a non running R100/7 with ~60k miles. Here's the story:The bike was running when I got it but had some serious oil leaks and was just dirty. I stripped it to the frame, cleaned parts, sanded and painted the frame, and replaced multiple parts. I put it back together and now it will not start and I can't figure out why and I'm leaving for school soon. It cranks freely, and even starts on a warm day with starter fluid and full choke. It will rev and idle fairly well, but if you turn it off and let it cool, it's the same story. Here's what I have done:-cleaned and replaced gaskets and orings for both carbs-replaced oil pan gasket-replaced and set ignition points and condenser-replaced battery-replaced spark plugs-replaced various orings and gaskets around the cylinders-replaced missing gas cap and removed most of the rust inside the tankNow for the bad: -still leaks a little bit of oil around left cylinder head when running-leaks a minor amount of gas on left petcock-left exhaust burns oil when running-some wiring problems (turn signals don't work. may just be the bulbs though)-Exhaust pipes have lots of rust-tank has multiple dents and scratches.-headlight doesnt really fit in the headlight housing (is either missing parts or or is the wrong headlight)-forks need oil-and of course the big one is that is does not startIt has good compression, spark, and the timing should be close enough to start. My suspicion is that not enough fuel is getting to the engine. Now I know you're probably offended that I want $1800 for its current condition, but these are hard to find and getting increasingly popular, especially with the cafe racer crowd. I'd be willing to trade for another motorcycle as well.
